<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 3:59AM CDT  by NWS Wichita</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Marion
County through 430 AM CDT...
At 358 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Marion, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Marion, Florence, Pilsen and Marion Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
